column5: Okay Im freaking and peaking Im bouncing of walls talking giberish and all sweaty Ineed a fix hurry up Wenesday and let me leave the southern nightmare!!!!!!!
I gets worse Pete. I can't be there till Friday.
Don't peak too early Pete.........!
Ill be going over Thursday to see whats going on.. then Im there till sunday...
Wanna turn my blankies down TJ?

I'll be there Wed, but wish I were there now, saw Big Chev and Lady Walley all loaded up and on there way today.  I just hope the southern contingents up there by now, the 400 is closed yet again for a couple of hours  Hey TJ, are Monique and the kids coming this year?  I've seen no mention of them yet...  Maureen

The plummas spent Sunday eve in Barrie, having made great time yesterday.  Greencoachdog hit the 400 at daybreak from Toronto, and should be enjoying a cool sparkling beverage right about now with Joe and Art.  I can't see how this could possibly help with those ants in pants, but, there ya go.

Personally, I am probably not going to be there until mid thursday now. Am attending a funeral tuesday afternoon(was supposed to leave at 10 am tuesday morning). Now, I will not leave until wednesday morning. I might get up early wednesday, and drive straight through the 12 hrs., but I doubt it.  Sent a message to the lakair e-mail address about this also, hope the southern contingent gets the message a.s.a.p.  Tom
Ok I am jealous... have a blast guys!  Cheers  Jen
Thay will be there for at least the Saturday.. were still figuring it out...
I'm sorry to hear that Tom, but you should be able to drive for 12 hrs....it's worth the drive to Lakair
The wife and I are arriving before noon on Thursday and my son Toothycritter will be comming in on Friday, can't wait to see everyone
Looking forward to seeing you and your family too, Tom.
I can believe that Mo, I am just not used to driving long distances by my lonesome self. Gotta take that into account.
We recently got a trade in that will allow me to go on Saturday morning. Its a little bigger than my boat with a CUDDY. So a Saturday night party is ON!!! Yahoo- cant wait either.
Great news Bernie    , you won't be sorry...well maybe you will be Sunday morning  Maureen
Who ever is staying with or near Peter beware he snores as loud as a Chainsaw and the ground trembles like a passing freight train.Don't forget your ear plugs

Bly and I are dropping our kids off around 8am on Friday.  Should be on the road by 9.  Looking at a map, it looks like it's about a 500km drive.  Hopefully pulling in at 3ish in the afternoon.  If anyone sees Gerritt before then, please let him know...thanks!!!  See you all up there.
Cliff, from Richmond Hill we make it in about 3 1/2 to 4 hours, depending on traffic.  Joey
Joey,do I have to bring the First aid kit again  See you guys soon.  Steve
Well it might be a good idea Steve, but I'll try to be a little more careful this time.  Maybe I'll dig out the boga grippers this time  Joey
Cool...I figured I'd put a worse case scenario in saying 6 hours.  We'll be coming up the east side of Simcoe...take hwy 12 to 400 then up 69.  With a bit of luck we'll be there by 2ish then.
Peter,I know your anxious to get up to Lakair,but do not forget to bring you know what.Your time is up  Steve
Pointed(Bill) is looking foward a little piece of brass amongst greatness
I still havent washed my hand Steve but you can smell my finger when I get there
